is that we should have a periodic
check in with our stakeholders.

29
00:01:53.918 --> 00:01:57.726
And in those conversations,
they're gonna expect to see more and

30
00:01:57.726 --> 00:01:59.972
more value created over time, right?

31
00:01:59.972 --> 00:02:03.706
So each time that I sit down maybe
this is quarterly, or monthly, or

32
00:02:03.706 --> 00:02:06.931
whatever your cadence is,
each time I sit down with them.

33
00:02:06.931 --> 00:02:11.161
I should plan to be able to show here's
where we've created value based on

34
00:02:11.161 --> 00:02:12.948
the investment you've made.

35
00:02:12.948 --> 00:02:15.049
And here's where we're headed, right?

36
00:02:15.049 --> 00:02:20.423
Now, if we plot out sort of Rick Rubin's
idea of the idea versus the reality,

37
00:02:20.423 --> 00:02:22.821
or the unearthly and the earthly,

38
00:02:22.821 --> 00:02:26.975
we might get something that
looks kinda like this, right?

39
00:02:26.975 --> 00:02:29.804
So the thing that I'm selling, this idea,

40
00:02:29.804 --> 00:02:33.322
this sort of aspirational concept,
is always ahead,

41
00:02:33.322 --> 00:02:37.765
it's always a little bit better [LAUGH],
